SIMPLE: printer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Printer
<hw>Print"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who prints;
especially, one who prints books, newspapers, engravings, etc., a
compositor; a typesetter; a pressman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Printer's devil</b></col>, <col><b>Printer's
gauge</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See under <er>Devil</er>, and
<er>Gauge</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Printer's ink</b></col>. <cd>See
<cref>Printing ink</cref>, below.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Printery</ent>⟦br⟧
